name: diadenylate cyclase
comment: Cyclic di-3',5'-adenylate is a bioactive molecule produced by some bacteria and archaea, which may function as a secondary signalling molecule [1]. The intracellular bacterial pathogen Listeria monocytogenes secretes it into the host's cytosol, where it triggers a cytosolic pathway of innate immunity [2].

references.title: Structural biochemistry of a bacterial checkpoint protein reveals diadenylate cyclase activity regulated by DNA recombination intermediates.
c-di-AMP secreted by intracellular Listeria monocytogenes activates a host type I interferon response.
